fields.descriptive_line: Set of silk skeins for embroidery in various colours, China, 1880-1910
fields.physical_description: Set of 56 skeins of multi-coloured silk for embroidery. The thread has a negligible twist and is very glossy. Each set of skeins is housed in a blue printed paper package. The set has a paper packing and a label in Chinese.
fields.production_note: According to donor, who gave it in 1968, she herself had received the skeins at least 50 years before.
